<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLATFORM; 
</P>
<P>
COLOR BLIND AT THE FRONT LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES E. McGEE was one of the first black fighter pilots to serve in World 
War II and later in the Korean and Vietnam wars. He believes that U.S. military 
presence in the Middle East is justified. He told The Times: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a veteran and from my viewpoint, I think we have a very touchy situation in 
(the Middle East) and one that will probably be hard for people to understand 
if people get killed. It would probably be difficult for those who are not 
privy to all of the intelligence that goes into making these decisions of when 
we ought to use military power and this just happens to be the case. 
</P>
<P>
The President has chosen that option. 
</P>
<P>
Blacks are Americans and a part of this country. We hope that there will be no 
significance made between black or white (military men and women during the 
crisis). We hope that they would carry out the job that is required. 
</P>
<P>
Our services for a great number of years have been made up of volunteer forces, 
not drafted forces. And perhaps a greater number of blacks have volunteered to 
serve, even if a great proportion were on the front lines in Vietnam. If they 
have been accepted on equal standards and can carry out the job, I think they 
would perform just as well. 
</P>
<P>
They are not in (the Persian Gulf) because someone is sending blacks to be the 
first to be killed. They are there because they volunteered to support this 
country and to help keep the military power of this country great. I really 
think this is often something that our populous doesn't understand and that is 
related to this, no war has been declared (in the Persian Gulf) but certainly 
military power is one of the options that our President has to keep this 
country free to keep its allies protected. 
</P>
<P>
Whoever that soldier is who has volunteered and is qualified to carry out that 
duty at the front line, he has to be color blind. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
