WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EAST GERMANY; 
</P>
<P>
WEST'S ULTRA-RIGHT PARTY IS REGISTERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Germany's right-wing Republican Party has been registered as a legitimate 
political organization in the East, authorities in East Berlin said. 
</P>
<P>
Several political and anti-fascist groups had objected to accepting the party 
founded in the early 1980s by a former member of Adolf Hitler's elite Waffen SS 
troops. The party first won seats in West Berlin city elections in January, 
1989, after campaigning on an anti-immigration platform. The East German 
Committee of Anti-Fascist Resistance Fighters had opposed recognition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
