<TEXT>
<P>
Pakistan said its armed forces repulsed an attack by Indian troops along the 
cease-fire line that divides the disputed territory of Kashmir. 
</P>
<P>
India denied the claim. Pakistan's defense ministry said the attack on a remote 
observation post in the Himalayas occurred over the weekend, after talks ended 
between the two countries to ease border tensions. Officials said Indian troops 
used heavy artillery, anti-tank guns and mortars in an attempt to capture an 
outpost in the Kel sector of Pakistan-controlled Kashmir. 
</P>
