<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet diplomat expelled for alleged meddling in Egypt's internal affairs has 
returned to Cairo nine years later to take up his old post of ambassador. 
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Polyakov, director of the Middle East and North African department at 
the Soviet Foreign Ministry, was expelled in 1981 by then-President Anwar Sadat 
who accused him of inciting strife in Egypt. 
