<P>
PARTY CRASHERS STAB FLEEING TEEN-AGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CAROL WATSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Camarillo teen-ager was stabbed in the back as he attempted to run from 
several attackers at a party in Thousand Oaks, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old boy was stabbed with a knife during a fight that broke out 
about 9:30 p.m. Saturday between guests and people trying to crash the party in 
the 2700 block of Amber Wood Place, Ventura County Sheriff's Sgt. Dan Coons 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Two young men tried to enter the party and were refused. They returned with 15 
to 20 others armed with clubs and began chasing the guests, Coons said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was taken to Los Robles Regional Medical Center in Thousand Oaks, 
where he was treated and released. CAROL WATSON 
