<P>
2 BODIES FOUND IN CRASHED PLANE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura County Sheriff's Department, making a routine helicopter flight 
over the Los Padres National Forest on Monday, found a crashed plane and two 
bodies believed to be missing for at least a month, officials said. 
</P>
