<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLORENCE MANDEL; CHAMBER OF COMMERCE MANAGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Florence Mandel of Arleta, a former manager with the Panorama City/Sepulveda 
Chamber of Commerce, has died at Encino Hospital. She was 68. 
</P>
<P>
Born Florence Jaslow in Mt. Clemens, Mich., she died Saturday of cancer, said 
Max Mandel, her husband of 46 years. 
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Mandel came to the San Fernando Valley in 1955 with her family. She became 
active in the Girl Scouts and was the coordinator for the Northeast Valley 
chapter for more than 15 years. She was also an active member of the 
Beautification Committee for the San Fernando Valley, as well as the Pacoima 
Women's Club and the Police Athletic League. 
</P>
<P>
She began working as a manager for the Pacoima Chamber of Commerce in 1974. She 
continued as manager at the Reseda Chamber of Commerce from 1976 through 1980, 
and retired from the Panorama City/Sepulveda Chamber of Commerce after working 
there from 1981 through 1984. 
</P>
<P>
She is survived by her husband, Max Mandel; daughters Charlene Mandel-Chadwick 
of Pleasant Hill, Barbara Mandel of Palmdale and Sandy Mandel of Pacoima; a 
brother, Charles Jaslow of Sun City, Ariz.; and sisters Tillie Klein of Sun 
City, Ariz., Elizabeth Rauch of Boca Raton, Fla., and Sylvia Spitzer of Boca 
Raton, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
A funeral service was held Monday at Sholom Mortuary in San Fernando, where the 
arrangements were made. Donations can be made in Mrs. Mandel's name to the 
American Cancer Society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
