<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Laker guard Michael Cooper seems to have one foot in Italy and the other in the 
NBA. 
</P>
<P>
"We must only wait for a few days for the actual signing," Valerio Bianchini, 
coach of Il Messaggero of Rome, told a sports newspaper in Milan. "Cooper is 
practically in our hands." 
</P>
<P>
But the Lakers said no decision on Cooper has been made. Last week it was 
reported that the Lakers are planning to put Cooper on waivers Wednesday. Any 
NBA team would have 48 hours to claim him at his salary of a little more than 
$600,000. If all teams pass, Cooper would be free to accept the Il Messaggero 
offer. 
</P>
