REGIONAL EARNINGS: INTERNATIONAL REMOTE TRIMS QUARTERLY NET LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
International Remote Imaging Systems Inc., a Chatsworth manufacturer of 
urinalysis machines, said it narrowed its net loss to $85,945 in the second 
quarter that ended June 30 from $745,963 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Revenues increased 34% to $1.14 million from $854,071. 
</P>
<P>
For the six months that ended in June, International Remote lost $144,348, 
compared to a net loss of $1.14 million in the year-earlier period. Revenues 
were $2.22 million, an 18% gain from $1.89 million a year before. International 
Remote said the narrower losses reflected increased product sales and revenues 
from research and development, and decreases in operating expenses. 
</P>
