<HEADLINE>
<P>
MARTIN MARIETTA GETS JET CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BETHESDA, Md. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Martin Marietta Corp. said it has received a $185-million contract to produce 
an additional 400 jet engine-thrust reversers for GE Aircraft Engines' CF6-80C2 
turbofan engines. 
</P>
<P>
Martin Marietta Aero &amp; Naval Systems at Baltimore will produce the fan 
reversers, with delivery scheduled to begin in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
The CF6-80C2 engines are installed in the Boeing 747 and 767, McDonnell Douglas 
MD-11, and Airbus Industries A300 and A310 airliners, the company said. 
</P>
