<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 14-YEAR-OLD BOY, SHOT BY FRIEND IN 
ACCIDENT, DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 14-year-old boy who was accidentally shot by a friend last week as they 
played with a gun died early Monday of his wounds, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The boy, identified as Donnell Arsene, was shot in the head late Thursday with 
a small-caliber revolver, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Arsene and a group of youths were playing with the weapon outside the boy's 
home on East 80th Street in South Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Arsene died at 6:05 a.m. Monday at Martin Luther King Jr./Drew Medical Center, 
Detective James Harper said. Harper said that while the investigation 
continues, all indications so far are that the shooting was accidental and no 
charges will be filed. 
</P>
<P>
"All of the witnesses corroborate each other's statements," Harper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SHOOTING ACCIDENTS -- LOS ANGELES; ACCIDENT VICTIMS; JUVENILE CRIMINALS; 
MURDERS -- LOS ANGELES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
