TICKETS, PLEASE: The Irvine Barclay Theatre is giving new meaning to the term 
"advance sales." . . . Tickets are already available for the 750-seat theater 
on the edge of the UC Irvine campus, even though it's still under construction. 
Because the theater is the size of a small Broadway playhouse, "we encourage 
people to purchase their tickets early to make sure they get seats," says UCI's 
Barbara Davidson. . . . The first performance, Nov. 2, will feature the Bella 
Lewitzky Dance Co. introducing a dance honoring UCI's 25th anniversary. 
