<TEXT>
<P>
SUDS UP: Beach Beer Inc. of Newport Beach makes beer in Dubuque, Iowa, that it 
calls "Trestles Lager," after the South County beach that took its name from 
the nearby rail line. 
</P>
<P>
Other surf labels include "Zuma" and "Rincon.". . . Company President Michael 
Imeson, who used to surf here as a teen-ager, now works out of Seattle and 
hasn't surfed at Trestles in six years. Still, he says he is donating 1% of 
Trestles' gross profits for beach protection, "to have some vehicle to make 
sure those beaches stay surfable for years to come." Kristina Lindgren and John 
Needham 
