<P>
SCHOOL TRUSTEE SELECTION TUESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After two weeks of interviewing candidates to fill a vacancy on the Huntington 
Beach Union High School District board, trustees are scheduled today to decide 
who their new colleague will be. 
</P>
<P>
Board members plan to interview seven finalists from an original field of 16 
candidates before appointing a replacement for David Warfield, who resigned in 
June. 
</P>
<P>
Fourteen of the original candidates showed up for interviews at last week's 
board meeting to explain their educational philosophies and why they want to 
become trustees. Board members will query the remaining candidates on more 
detailed issues at Tuesday's meeting, scheduled for 7 p.m. at district offices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
