<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: SCIENCE/TECHNOLOGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Dean Takahashi, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Symbiotic Relationship: Sterling Microsystems Inc., an Anaheim computer 
company, said Monday that it has entered into a joint reseller agreement with 
Tricord Systems Inc. in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
The deal is valued at more than $2 million, the companies said. 
</P>
<P>
Tricord develops and markets network server equipment that Sterling will sell 
in marketing its computer network applications to business and engineering 
customers. 
</P>
<P>
"Our agreement with Sterling Microsystems is another step in our strategic plan 
to develop a strong, competent distribution channel," said Tricord President 
James D. Edwards. "Sterling's goals for promoting networking applications are a 
perfect match." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
