<HEADLINE>
<P>
SDSU GOES TO MARKET HOME FOOTBALL GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT MILLER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
San Diego State launched its new marketing campaign Monday in an attempt to 
increase attendance at Aztec home football games. 
</P>
<P>
The theme is "Welcome to the School of Hard Knocks," and the campaign includes 
promotions for each of the Aztecs' six home games as well as schedule posters 
and cards with the "Clash Schedule" and a special mailing to SDSU alumni 
encouraging them to purchase season football tickets by enrolling in the 
"Aztecs' Refresher Course -- Six Saturdays, No Final Exam." 
</P>
<P>
"We are going to add to the fun of an Aztec football evening with promotions 
and activities around each home game," said Jayne Hancock, associate director 
of athletics. 
</P>
<P>
To that end, here is the SDSU home schedule, along with corresponding 
promotions: 
</P>
<P>
* Sept. 15, Cal State Long Beach -- Fans will receive a free slice of pizza if 
the 49ers and Aztecs combine to score higher than Cal State Long Beach Coach 
George Allen's age (72). There will be George Allen trivia contests throughout 
the game on the DiamondVision scoreboard, fireworks after the game, and mascot 
Monty Montezuma's new pregame entrance will debut on this night. 
</P>
<P>
* Sept. 29, Air Force -- There will be a paper airplane toss before the game. 
Hit a target, win a prize. There will also be a postgame concert. 
</P>
<P>
* Nov. 3, Utah -- Homecoming and free pompons. 
</P>
<P>
* Nov. 10, Hawaii -- It's beach party night. Fans will be asked to wear beach 
clothes, which will make them look like the band. The scoreboard will feature 
beach music and beach movie clips. 
</P>
<P>
* Nov. 24, Texas-El Paso -- A country carnival will begin at San Diego Jack 
Murphy Stadium at 3 p.m. The scoreboard will feature country and western music 
and Western movie clips. 
</P>
<P>
* Dec. 1, Miami -- This is "Salute to College Football Night," and a fireworks 
and laser show will take place after the game against defending national 
champion Miami. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081490-0152 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 261744 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 14, 1990, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
