<P>
'90 MOVIE TALLY TOPS $3 BILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moviegoers have shelled out more than $3 billion so far this year at the 
domestic box office, just 2 percent behind the record-setting pace set last 
year, when the final tally topped $5 billion. 
</P>
<P>
With the surprise hits "Ghost" and "Die Hard 2" leading the way this summer, 
the year-to-date box office total hit $3.08 billion over the weekend, compared 
to $3.14 billion for the same period last year. In 1988, the total at this 
point in the year had reached $2.78 billion. 
</P>
<P>
Disney's "Pretty Woman" led all films this year with a gross of $165.8 million 
in 21 weeks of release, followed by New Line's "Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles," 
at $132.2 million in 20 weeks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
