ROLLE REMAINS IN INTENSIVE CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Esther Rolle remained in serious but stable condition today at the 
hospital where she is being treated for injuries suffered in a car crash 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Rolle, 69, remained in the intensive care unit of University Medical Center. 
She suffered cuts of the head and face, fractured ribs and a bruised heart. 
</P>
<P>
Rolle's credits include the television series "Good Times" and the movie 
"Driving Miss Daisy." 
</P>
<P>
She was a passenger in a car that rolled over on Interstate 15 near the 
California border, killing the driver, Paulene Hopkins, 70, of Marshall, Tex. 
