LUKAS AIMS AT 3RD SANFORD STAKES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SARATOGA SPRINGS, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Trainer D. Wayne Lukas will be seeking his third Sanford Stakes winner in the 
last six years Wednesday when his entry of Formal Dinner and Radio Daze heads a 
field of 10 colts and geldings. 
</P>
<P>
The six-furlong race features a purse of $92,100, with $55,260 going to the 
winner. 
</P>
<P>
Lukas won the Sanford last year with Bite the Bullet and in 1985 with Sovereign 
Don. 
</P>
<P>
Formal Dinner, who will carry 115 pounds and jockey Jose Santos, set a track 
record for 5 1/2 furlongs at Churchill Downs 1:04:2 in a nine-length victory. 
