<HEADLINE>
<P>
TROTTING, PACING CHAMPIONS CROWNED AT FAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPRINGFIELD, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Federal Arsenal and Cody won trotting championships, and Styling and Lake Hills 
Texas were crowned pacing champions Monday on the first day of the Illinois 
State Fair's five-day harness-racing meet. 
</P>
<P>
The start of Monday's 15-race card was delayed two hours by overnight rains. 
</P>
<P>
The track officially was listed as good, yet 11 of the 15 heats went in under 
2:00. 
</P>
<P>
Federal Arsenal arrived in Springfield with just one victory in seven starts 
but cruised to victory in the $53,700 event for 2-year-old trotters. 
</P>
<P>
Cody's success came as no surprise in the $42,700 race for 3-year-old trotting 
colts. Cody won two straight heats and pushed the horse's record to seven 
victories in 12 starts. 
</P>
<P>
Styling, likewise, was no surprise winner -- except that he almost didn't 
qualify for the race. After going off stride in his elimination heat and 
lagging far behind, Styling caught the leaders past the half-mile mark only to 
finish sixth -- the farthest back he could finish and still qualify for the 
race. 
</P>
<P>
Styling won in 1:55.4. 
</P>
<P>
Owned by Gary Williams and Michael Salter of Davenport and Bettendrorf, Iowa, 
Styling owns nine victories in 11 starts. 
</P>
<P>
The day's biggest upset came in the $48,000 event for 3-year-old pacers. Lake 
Hills Texas won in 1:56 and returned $58.40, 9.20 and 6.40. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
